02:32.917 --> 02:35.166
Here I come!

02:35.167 --> 02:36.957
Here I come.

02:36.959 --> 02:38.079
Mrs Faulkner?

02:38.084 --> 02:40.134
Yes. Bella Faulkner.

02:41.542 --> 02:45.502
Bella, Paula Hall from Child Welfare
Services. This is Ricky Baker.

02:45.503 --> 02:47.916
Ricky Baker. Yes.

02:47.917 --> 02:51.287
Oh, here you are.

02:51.501 --> 02:53.081
Mm.

02:55.209 --> 02:59.128
Ricky, I'm Bella. Uh, you can call
me Bella, or Auntie, if you like,

02:59.129 --> 03:01.076
even though I'm not
your real auntie.

03:01.084 --> 03:03.916
But, you know, it's
a bit less formal.

03:03.917 --> 03:05.577
Whoo. You're a big fella!

03:05.584 --> 03:10.004
Who ate the guy who
ate all the pies, eh?

03:11.001 --> 03:12.001
Sorry.

03:12.751 --> 03:14.421
Well, he's nice.

03:14.792 --> 03:18.042
Yeah. Now, uh, obviously we've got a
couple of things to talk through, Bella.

03:18.084 --> 03:22.384
Clearly you've been briefed about his, uh,
background and also his foster care history.

03:22.417 --> 03:24.787
Apparently he's a bit of
a handful, a real bad egg.

03:24.834 --> 03:27.464
I mean, if you look at his file,
you'll see that for yourself.

03:27.501 --> 03:31.791
We're talking disobedience, stealing,
spitting, running away,

03:31.792 --> 03:36.791
throwing rocks, kicking stuff, defacing
stuff, burning stuff, loitering and graffiti.

03:36.792 --> 03:38.922
And that's just the
stuff we know about.

03:39.042 --> 03:42.752
But hopefully, uh, change in scene
will help straighten him out.

03:43.334 --> 03:45.134
He's home now. He'll be OK.

03:45.167 --> 03:48.417
OK. Well, I like your
enthusiasm. Good.

04:00.709 --> 04:03.249
Ricky, this is your new home.

04:03.542 --> 04:05.292
A real piece of work, this one.

04:05.417 --> 04:06.667
Ricky!

04:08.167 --> 04:10.877
There's no one else
who wants you, OK?

04:10.917 --> 04:15.247
Now, Ricky, you know what the
alternative is, don't you? Eh?

04:16.709 --> 04:20.829
Think you can make it work? 'Course we can.
We'll make it work.

04:28.709 --> 04:31.419
Move. Move it. Move!

04:32.792 --> 04:34.922
Yeah. I've been in
this game a long time.

04:34.959 --> 04:36.579
'No child left behind' is our motto.

04:36.626 --> 04:39.996
Well, it's not, you know, the official
motto, but it's definitely mine.

04:40.042 --> 04:43.632
Also, as part of the transition process,
I'll be needing to inspect your property,

04:43.667 --> 04:46.416
just to make sure that it's
up to our high standard.

04:46.417 --> 04:48.827
Looks fine. What do you think,
Constable Tappert?

04:49.792 --> 04:52.582
- Andy!
- Yeah, it looks cool.Yeah.

04:52.626 --> 04:56.746
We'll be coming in every eight weeks or so,
just to check in on, uh...

05:01.167 --> 05:03.247
Who's that Crocodile Dundee
guy over there?

05:03.251 --> 05:05.711
Oh, that's my husband, Hector.

05:05.751 --> 05:08.751
Whoa. He's giving
that pig a piggyback.

05:12.209 --> 05:17.129
Well, I see he has a rifle. Just
keep it away from this little guy.

05:17.542 --> 05:19.422
God knows what he's capable of.

05:19.876 --> 05:22.375
OK, he's all yours. No returns.

05:22.376 --> 05:24.036
Oh, I'm just joking.

05:24.042 --> 05:27.882
OK. You've got my number, so just, uh,
ring me if you've got any trouble. OK?

05:28.334 --> 05:29.384
Bye, Ricky.

05:31.584 --> 05:32.754
Bye, Ricky.

05:33.959 --> 05:35.579
Wow, what a shocker, eh

05:36.251 --> 05:38.081
OK, let's go, Andy.

05:44.459 --> 05:48.079
Ricky, this is Hec. You can
call him Uncle, if you like.

05:49.751 --> 05:51.421
No, he can't.

05:54.376 --> 05:56.746
What do you want to do?
Are you hungry?

05:57.751 --> 06:01.171
That's a silly question,
isn't it? Look at you.

06:22.501 --> 06:24.831
Mm?

06:30.126 --> 06:35.496
You ever worked on a farm before
or you just... ornamental?

06:36.834 --> 06:40.543
Hec. Just remember when we first met,
you weren't much good to anyone.

06:40.544 --> 06:43.792
Just a scruffy white drifter who
smelled like methylated spirits.

06:44.459 --> 06:45.709
Goodnight.

06:46.126 --> 06:48.076
Eh? What's that, dear?

06:49.376 --> 06:51.376
Goodnight.

06:52.792 --> 06:53.962
Oh...

06:55.501 --> 06:57.421
Jeez, Hec. You bloody idiot.

06:57.501 --> 06:58.541
What?

07:01.792 --> 07:02.792
Ricky?

07:03.459 --> 07:05.829
Buddy? Are you OK?

07:06.334 --> 07:09.504
Sorry about Hec. He's a
silly old goat, that's all.

07:10.417 --> 07:13.667
OK, well, I hope you
like your room, petal.

07:13.709 --> 07:16.918
They said you liked to read, so
I got a bunch of books for you,

07:16.919 --> 07:21.417
and you'll also notice an Indian lamp,
a bulldog lamp and some cats,

07:21.459 --> 07:24.329
and a nice sharp knife to
kill monsters in the night.

07:24.376 --> 07:27.727
I can't imagine what you've been through,
boy. You know, I can't imagine it was easy.

07:27.751 --> 07:29.711
But you're here now.
This is home.

07:30.626 --> 07:35.706
Anyway, it's really nice to have
you here, and I left a hottie in your bed.

07:35.751 --> 07:37.751
We'll see you in the morning.

07:38.542 --> 07:39.542
OK?

07:40.792 --> 07:42.082
OK, Ricky?

07:42.917 --> 07:43.917
OK.

07:44.917 --> 07:47.077
Nigh-night, then.
See you in the morning.

08:59.917 --> 09:05.917
Jeez, boy, it's a miracle we found you!
You made it all of 200m.

09:08.001 --> 09:09.791
I was just taking a break.

09:10.667 --> 09:12.247
Hec's cooking breakfast.

09:13.417 --> 09:19.077
Eggs, bacon, a few sossies
on the side,... pancakes.

09:21.751 --> 09:26.961
Come on. Have some breakfast,
then you can run away.

09:36.959 --> 09:39.919
Oh man. I got poop on my kicks.

09:41.292 --> 09:43.542
Go away, insect!

09:49.042 --> 09:51.672
Good pancake.

09:53.792 --> 09:56.002
So, what's your dog's name?

09:56.876 --> 09:57.956
Zag.

09:58.334 --> 10:00.794
You should get another
one and name it Zig.

10:03.542 --> 10:07.752
Bella told me to tell you that...
you should give me something to do.

10:07.753 --> 10:09.421
Is there anything
you want me to do?

10:09.584 --> 10:13.174
Yeah,... leave me alone.

10:16.292 --> 10:17.462
Cool.

11:01.126 --> 11:02.166
Morning.

11:02.167 --> 11:05.457
Morning. I thought
you were running away.

11:06.001 --> 11:09.331
I did, but I forgot something,
so I came back.

11:09.376 --> 11:13.326
Oh. Good for you, Ricky.
Good to see some initiative.

11:16.167 --> 11:18.287
You ever been up in
that jungle before?

11:18.501 --> 11:22.961
Oh, it's not a jungle; it's the bush. There's
about a million hectares of it, buddy.

11:23.167 --> 11:25.457
You said 'bush'.

11:26.126 --> 11:28.916
I'm from up there,
deep in the mountains.

11:29.209 --> 11:30.629
You ever go back much? Not for

11:30.667 --> 11:34.377
a long time. It's a
hard journey, easy to get lost.

11:34.626 --> 11:37.206
We got a lake up there
called Makutekahu.

11:37.542 --> 11:40.382
It's so high up it wets
the cloak of the sky.

11:40.459 --> 11:43.879
It's the first place our spirits
go on their way to Reinga.

11:44.334 --> 11:48.004
Yeah, when my time comes,
that's where I'll go too.

11:49.751 --> 11:52.500
Man, you guys got a lot
of dead stuff round here.

11:52.501 --> 11:56.501
Mm. Saw a dead sheep the other day.
Had maggots in it.

11:57.251 --> 11:59.961
There's heaps of maggots,

12:00.334 --> 12:03.384
maggots wriggling in that sheep

12:03.751 --> 12:08.081
like moving rice. Yuck.

12:09.042 --> 12:12.962
That was my haiku about maggots.

12:13.084 --> 12:15.044
It's called 'Maggots'.

12:15.667 --> 12:20.417
This counsellor lady made me
do them when I got in trouble.

12:20.501 --> 12:23.041
They help me express
my feelings.

12:23.042 --> 12:26.132
They're poems made up of...
Yeah. I know what a haiku is.

12:27.209 --> 12:30.379
I got heaps of them...
want to hear another one?

12:30.417 --> 12:31.077
Sure.

12:31.251 --> 12:33.211
OK.

12:34.042 --> 12:35.632
'Kingi, you wanker.

12:35.751 --> 12:38.711
'You arsehole.
I hate you heaps.

12:39.167 --> 12:41.577
'Please die soon in pain.'

12:42.292 --> 12:44.882
That was called
'Kingi, you Wanker'.

12:44.917 --> 12:47.917
Yeah, yeah. OK. Got ya. Got ya.
That's enough haikus for today.

12:48.542 --> 12:50.962
Come on. Sit down.
Come and give me a hand.

12:52.709 --> 12:54.749
Well, it's like this,

12:55.917 --> 12:59.417
and then you put it in this bag.

12:59.542 --> 13:00.632
Easy.

13:01.334 --> 13:02.634
Here you go. You have a go.

13:06.084 --> 13:07.754
Do you want to
try something else?

13:08.292 --> 13:09.502
Yes, please.

13:11.584 --> 13:16.504
I'm imagining I'm a Maori warrior, and that
bottle over there is a British soldier,

13:16.505 --> 13:18.961
and I'm defending all my wives.

13:19.542 --> 13:21.708
All right, Te Kooti.

13:21.709 --> 13:25.459
Well, you just keep the target above
the little notch in the sight.

13:25.501 --> 13:27.881
And then when you're ready,
you just breathe...

13:29.709 --> 13:30.919
Bloody hell!

13:31.501 --> 13:32.631
So, what are we hunting?

13:32.632 --> 13:36.326
Oh, anything.
Deer, if we're lucky.

13:36.376 --> 13:38.536
Can we shoot one of
those horses up there?

13:38.542 --> 13:40.832
Oh, I'll give... I'll give you one
guess what my answer will be.

13:40.834 --> 13:43.294
Well, can I ride one?

13:43.334 --> 13:46.794
Nobody can ride them;
they're too wild.

13:46.834 --> 13:48.504
Why do they need
to be ridden, anyway?

13:48.542 --> 13:50.379
Well, that's what
they're there for.

13:50.380 --> 13:53.876
Why can't they just eat grass and
be horses and leave it at that, eh?

13:53.917 --> 13:56.287
OK, OK. I was just
making conversation.

13:56.292 --> 13:57.382
ZAG BARKS Shh.

13:58.584 --> 14:00.674
Pig! Come on!

14:00.709 --> 14:02.249
What?

14:30.292 --> 14:33.712
Whoo-hoo-hoo-hoo!
That's dinner sorted!

14:33.959 --> 14:35.789
Whoa! Want to help me gut it?

14:41.167 --> 14:43.667
♪ Ricky Baker, now
you are 13 years old.

14:43.709 --> 14:47.709
♪ You are a teenager,
and you're as good as gold.

14:48.334 --> 14:50.884
♪ Ricky Baker...

14:50.917 --> 14:55.247
♪ Ricky Baker, happy birthday.

14:55.292 --> 14:59.041
♪ Once rejected, now accepted

14:59.042 --> 15:03.212
♪ by me and Hector.

15:03.251 --> 15:06.711
♪ We're a trifecta.

15:06.751 --> 15:09.750
♪ Ricky Baker,
ah, Ricky Baker,

15:09.751 --> 15:11.458
♪ ah, Ricky Baker,

15:11.459 --> 15:13.129
♪ ah, ah, Ricky Baker, ah ah,

15:13.130 --> 15:17.496
♪ Ricky Baker, ah, ah,
Ricky Baker, ah, ah,

15:17.501 --> 15:22.921
♪ Ricky... Baker... ♪

15:26.334 --> 15:27.214
Hip hip!

15:27.215 --> 15:28.419
Hooray!

15:29.584 --> 15:31.044
Go on, blow out your candles.

15:31.459 --> 15:32.459
OK.

15:37.667 --> 15:43.167
Hector, do you think it's time
we gave Ricky his present?

15:55.542 --> 15:57.582
Thank you, Auntie!
Thank you, Uncle!

15:57.626 --> 16:01.536
Feed him, clean up after him.
He's yours... you're responsible.

16:01.542 --> 16:03.882
This is the best
birthday I've ever had.

16:05.126 --> 16:07.376
I think it's the only
birthday I've ever had.

16:11.917 --> 16:13.167
What are you gonna call him?

16:13.501 --> 16:17.421
Um, still thinking. Something fierce to
reflect its true nature.

16:17.626 --> 16:21.536
Either Psycho, Megatron...
or Tupac.

16:22.251 --> 16:23.581
What's a Tupac?

16:23.751 --> 16:27.751
It's just my... this really cool rapper,
and he's, like, my best friend.

16:29.917 --> 16:31.707
Are you gonna run away tonight?

16:32.792 --> 16:33.792
Not sure.

16:34.042 --> 16:35.882
No, oh, it's cool with me.

16:36.459 --> 16:38.629
Just make sure you're
back by breakfast.

16:40.001 --> 16:41.081
OK.

16:41.626 --> 16:44.076
So happy we found you, buddy.

16:44.126 --> 16:46.126
Sorry it took so long.

16:47.167 --> 16:48.167
Me too.

16:51.542 --> 16:52.791
Nigh-night, Ricky.

16:52.792 --> 16:54.542
Night, Auntie.

17:31.251 --> 17:34.041
Where are you going, Tupac?

17:35.751 --> 17:38.081
Come on.

17:38.542 --> 17:39.672
Man!

17:40.292 --> 17:41.962
Ohhh!

17:42.042 --> 17:43.752
Oh, Bella!

18:09.459 --> 18:11.749
You know, sometimes in life,

18:13.542 --> 18:15.502
it seems like
there's no way out...

18:17.584 --> 18:22.214
like a sheep trapped in
a maze designed by wolves.

18:23.584 --> 18:25.924
And you know that if
you're ever in that situation,

18:25.959 --> 18:28.879
there are always
two doors to choose from.

18:29.501 --> 18:30.881
And through the first door...

18:30.959 --> 18:33.289
oh, it's easy to get through that door
and on the other side waiting

18:33.292 --> 18:36.422
for you are all the nummiest
treats you can imagine.

18:36.459 --> 18:41.749
Fanta, Doritos, L&P,
Burger Rings, Coke Zero.

18:42.209 --> 18:44.629
But you know what?
There's also another door,

18:44.630 --> 18:47.706
not the Burger Ring door,
not the Fanta door;

18:47.751 --> 18:50.171
another door that's
harder to get through.

18:50.917 --> 18:52.787
Guess what's on the other side?

18:53.251 --> 18:55.251
Anyone want to take a guess?

18:57.959 --> 18:59.459
Vegetables?

19:01.126 --> 19:04.286
N-No, not vegeta...

19:05.542 --> 19:06.542
No.

19:07.709 --> 19:13.329
You would think Jesus. I thought Jesus the
first time I-I-I-I came across that door.

19:13.376 --> 19:15.916
It's not Jesus.
It's another door.

19:16.626 --> 19:19.166
And guess what's on the
other side of that door?

19:22.251 --> 19:23.251
Jesus.

19:23.501 --> 19:24.881
Jesus. Yeah, Jesus.

19:25.209 --> 19:27.039
He's tricky like that, Jesus.

19:28.376 --> 19:29.826
So let us pray,

19:30.376 --> 19:35.206
to Jesus, please, and make it a bit easier
to get through those doors, uh, to find you

19:35.209 --> 19:38.749
and your bounty of
delicious confectionary.

19:39.626 --> 19:41.576
Thank you, Selena.
Take it away.

21:00.376 --> 21:02.076
Dinner. It's a bit burnt.

21:10.667 --> 21:12.247
Here.

21:14.542 --> 21:15.792
Read this.

21:16.751 --> 21:18.881
Out loud.

21:20.917 --> 21:23.247
'From the
Child Welfare people.

21:23.792 --> 21:28.382
'Mr Hector Faulkner.'This is Paula
Hall from Child Welfare writing to you.

21:28.417 --> 21:30.707
'I'm sorry to hear about
your recent bereavement.

21:30.709 --> 21:33.669
'However, in light of
the altered circumstances,

21:33.709 --> 21:37.379
'the current situation regarding
Ricky's care will have to be reviewed.

21:37.417 --> 21:41.287
'As of June the 1st, I will be taking
him back into state custody

21:41.459 --> 21:43.829
'until alternative arrangements
can be made.

21:43.834 --> 21:47.294
'Rest assured I am working tireless
to find a new home for Ricky.

21:47.334 --> 21:52.254
'And you can expect a visit next
week for Ricky's collection.

21:52.292 --> 21:57.042
'Sincerely, Paula Hall,
Ministry of Child Welfare.'

21:57.709 --> 21:59.749
Like hell! They can't do that!

22:00.292 --> 22:01.666
Yeah, they can.

22:01.667 --> 22:05.127
But I live here now.
It's my home!

22:05.167 --> 22:10.287
Not any more, it isn't. Not in their eyes.
Not without a woman to run the show.

22:11.709 --> 22:15.669
Why don't we just get you a new wife?
There's plenty of ladies on the internet, I heard.

22:18.251 --> 22:19.381
Too soon?

22:19.459 --> 22:22.579
What if we just keep living here,
and if they try to take the farm,

22:22.626 --> 22:24.536
we'll just have a
shootout, like Scarface.

22:24.542 --> 22:26.129
Except we don't
have any cocaine.

22:26.130 --> 22:28.496
You can't change this, Ricky.
You're gonna go back,

22:28.584 --> 22:30.754
and you're gonna stick it out
in a new home. OK?

22:30.792 --> 22:32.502
There's no way that's happening.

22:32.709 --> 22:34.539
Well, I'm gonna go bush. I'm
gonna...

22:34.584 --> 22:36.504
...disappear for a while.

22:36.584 --> 22:40.174
Disappear?
Yeah, that sounds more like me.

22:42.167 --> 22:44.417
Come on! We'll be a team!

22:44.459 --> 22:47.289
Oh, for God's sake. You wouldn't
last five minutes out there.

22:47.751 --> 22:51.381
But Auntie Bella said
you had to look after me!

22:52.167 --> 22:54.037
Can you just give
me some privacy?

23:07.584 --> 23:10.424
I heard they do experiments
at the Boys' Home...

23:10.459 --> 23:12.669
waterboarding, torture,
that sort of thing.

23:12.709 --> 23:17.169
This one boy got thrown acid on his face
because he asked for more Weet-Bix.

23:18.792 --> 23:21.170
Hey, you can't put
Auntie in a box.

23:21.171 --> 23:23.417
Give it a rest. But she wanted to go
to the sky place.

23:23.459 --> 23:26.579
She's gone, OK? That's life...

23:27.459 --> 23:31.539
one day you're here, and the
next you're in a bloody box.

23:33.126 --> 23:35.996
Just get this into
your head, boy...

23:36.501 --> 23:39.581
it was Bella that wanted
you here, not me.

23:39.667 --> 23:42.537
I know you think this
can work, but it can't.

23:45.876 --> 23:49.746
So the welfare people are coming on Friday.
They're coming to get you.

23:52.584 --> 23:54.214
That's that, then?

23:54.251 --> 23:56.461
Yep... that's that.

24:23.792 --> 24:24.882
That's that.

24:57.376 --> 25:00.496
Goodbye, Ricky Baker.

25:04.459 --> 25:06.039
Uh-oh.

25:06.209 --> 25:09.379
Come on, Tupac! Come on, Tupac!

25:48.042 --> 25:53.502
♪ Out alone in the middle
of the ocean blue.

25:53.542 --> 25:54.832
Whoa!

25:54.834 --> 26:02.254
♪ Leave the world behind
I guess I never really knew.

26:03.209 --> 26:10.169
♪ So many people,
so many worlds.

26:10.209 --> 26:14.919
♪ Don't you worry about me.

26:17.834 --> 26:19.424
♪ Don't you worry about...

26:19.459 --> 26:24.209
Five down, 10 to go. Come on,
Ricky. Stick on the rations.

26:41.751 --> 26:48.291
♪ I belong in the middle
of the ocean blue.

26:49.292 --> 26:55.082
♪ I'm getting nowhere, but that
shouldn't really bother you.

26:56.959 --> 27:00.079
Stuff this,
Tupac. We're going home.

27:04.376 --> 27:08.456
♪ Don't you worry about me. ♪

27:24.251 --> 27:25.416
Are you lost?

27:25.417 --> 27:27.037
Oh!

27:27.334 --> 27:28.334
No.

27:28.542 --> 27:29.672
Yeah, you are.

27:30.376 --> 27:32.696
Told you you wouldn't last more
than five minutes out here.

27:33.626 --> 27:37.125
You got yourself very lost.
I'm amazed how lost you are.

27:37.126 --> 27:40.376
I move fast. I've got my
own thing going on here...

27:40.417 --> 27:43.207
Ricky Town.
Population... Ricky.

27:43.251 --> 27:45.671
Yeah, well. You're going
back to Reality Town.

27:45.672 --> 27:47.787
Like hell. I live here now.

27:47.876 --> 27:48.876
Like hell.

27:49.501 --> 27:52.831
I've got better things to do than to run around
the bush looking for little shits like you.

27:52.834 --> 27:53.674
So get up.

27:53.709 --> 27:54.329
I hate you.

27:54.334 --> 27:55.464
Well, I hate you too.

27:55.465 --> 27:56.579
I hope you die.

27:56.584 --> 27:57.294
Me too!

27:57.334 --> 27:59.634
You may as well just kill me now.

28:01.792 --> 28:03.002
Don't kill me.

28:05.626 --> 28:08.126
Anyway, I'm excited
to go back to the city.

28:08.709 --> 28:09.709
Good.

28:09.792 --> 28:12.922
Can't wait.
I hate it here...

